Type: Package
Package: catGenes
Title: Concatenating multiple DNA alignments and other phylogenetic features
Version: 1.0
Author: Domingos Cardoso and Quezia Cavalcante
Description: The catGenes package is intended to help researchers in phylogenetics and phylogenomics to build a fully concatenated or combined (non-interleaved) dataset by automatically comparing individual DNA alignments. Other features also involve mining DNA sequences or targeted loci from plastomes and mitochondrial genomes from GenBank, as well as plotting phylogenetic figures.
Maintainer: Domingos Cardoso <cardosobot@gmail.com>
URL: https://github.com/domingoscardoso/catGenes
Language: en-US
